  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our Children Our Future: Assessing Needs of Children in Domestic Labour</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Somalia, years of civil unrest, displacement, loss of parents due to HIV/AIDS and war, continue to drive children as young as five years old into a life of domestic servitude in the search for survival. In domestic servitude, children are vulnerable to exploitation and abuse. This project addresses the problem of domestic child labour in the Borama District. A Comic Relief grant will fund research into children involved in domestic labour to obtain evidence of the need and to cultivate opportunities to tackle the problem of domestic child labour. The research will inform strategies for the prevention of domestic child labour, exploitation and abuse; help to raise awareness about children at risk, and change attitudes and practices regarding the use of domestic child labour. The project will help to build the capacity of duty bearers and other relevant organisations to meet the needs of children and protect them from harm. It will strengthen the commitment to improve and uphold policies and practices that protect children at all levels, and improve the capacity of children to be consulted, heard and involved.</narrative>
  </description>
